<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This taxon has typical morphology of the 
<taxonomicName genus="Clavicipitaceae" lsidName="Clavicipitaceae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Clavicipitaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is pyriform perithecia with a gradually tapering upper part and cylindrical asci with a glassy refractive cap. New collections are required and need to be sequenced to clarify its placement.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
